          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "445 - وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "اُسْتُشْهِدَ حَنْظَلَةُ بْنُ أَبِي عَامِرٍ اَلرَّاهِبُ بِأُحُدٍ فَلَمْ يَأْمُرِ اَلنَّبِيُّ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "آلِهِ بِغُسْلِهِ وَقَالَ «رَأَيْتُ اَلْمَلاَئِكَةَ بَيْنَ اَلسَّمَاءِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " وَ "
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": "اَلْأَرْضِ تُغَسِّلُ، حَنْظَلَةَ بِمَاءِ اَلْمُزْنِ"
          },
          {
            "kind": "plain",
            "text": " فِي"
          }
        ]
      },
      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:25:47",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/25/445",
      "text": [
        " صِحَافٍ مِنْ فِضَّةٍ وَ كَانَ يُسَمَّى غَسِيلَ اَلْمَلاَئِكَةِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.445 - Hanzalah ibn Abu 'Amir, known as \"the Rahib,\" was martyred at the Battle of Uhud.\nThe Prophet Muhammad (sw) did not command that he be washed, saying: \"I saw the angels washing Hanzalah with water from the clouds, using silver vessels.\"\nBecause of this, he was given the title \"Ghasil al-Malaika\" (The One Washed by the Angels)."
        ]
      }
    },
    "verse_translations": [
